\maketitle
\begin{itemize}
\item Trials (stimuli) are organized into blocks to get semi-randomization:
\begin{itemize}
\item 16 blocks
\item Each block has 9 trials: 3 words from each valence, with 1 word for
each valence - color combination

The following table represents one block.

Table: block example
\end{itemize}
\end{itemize}

\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{llll}
\hline
text & letterColor & corrAns & condition\\
\hline
positiva1 & blue & right & positive\\
negativa1 & blue & right & negative\\
neutral1 & blue & right & neutral\\
positiva2 & green & down & positive\\
negativa2 & green & down & negative\\
neutral2 & green & down & neutral\\
positiva3 & red & left & positive\\
negativa3 & red & left & negative\\
neutral3 & red & left & neutral\\
\hline
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

\begin{itemize}
\item These blocks for randomization are organized into 3 large experimental
blocks
\item Participants are allowed 3 breaks to rest. One after completing every 36
trials (4 pseudo-randomization blocks). The participant continued by
pressing a key.
\item Conditions balanced in terms of word length
\end{itemize}
